@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

 So what is it ?

 Most programming languages have a function like MidStr or SubStr that returns
 a part of given length from a given string. The AmigaDOS Batch language however
 doesn't. So I've written a small shell tool providing that functionality. Though
 it's been done for personal use mainly, it might be useful for someone else. So
 I decided to release it. Here it is !

@endnode

